tried cooking it at 287 for about 25 minutes. It's fine and should contain minimal nitrosamines. 
    I see 275 for 30 minutes also being recommended. 
    for health purposes I probably will do it this way. 


___________________________________________

after experimentation I think 6 pieces on a sheet at 290 for 20 minutes is a very good amount. 
    the number of pieces does seem to make an impact. more pieces require more time. 
    not entirely sure why since the relative temperature of more bacon seems trivial compared to the oven. 
    maybe it's the proximity of the bacon. Although that explanation is still unsatisfying. 
    maybe it's the pan distributing its heat in a more dispersed manner due to there being more on it... 




